<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So doing more nuke damage to a mob than a mage does is less important than how big the nuke you are using to do the damage is?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes.  My guild has a senior wizard in it that ridicules me for my dps plan because I am focusing on Quick Damage and Subtlety before maxing crits.  I actually know several wizards that care more about big booms than the efficient booms. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teneran67>teneran67</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 5:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Yes. My guild has a senior wizard in it that ridicules me for my dps plan because I am focusing on Quick Damage and Subtlety before maxing crits. I actually know several wizards that care more about big booms than the efficient booms.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, crits ADD efficiency, btw.  When you have them maxed, about 18% of the time (over the long run) you'll do double damage, with no additional mana used.<br>
<br>
Quick damage does not add efficiency, on the other hand.  It does increase DPS for sure but its the same damage per mana whether you have it or not.<br>
<br>
As much as I love Spell Casting Subtlety, it also doesn't increase efficiency.  It increases potential DPS by giving us lower aggro per cast, since aggro often controls the rate at which we can nuke.  But again, damage per mana is uneffected.<br>
<br>
The AA skills that increase efficiency are crits, spell casting mastery, familiars (less fizzles supposedly) and possibly mastery of the past depending on the level spells you are casting (again less fizzles).<br>
<br>
Teneran<br>
