You have answered why not to use Ice Comet in your next sentence.  You and I know that Draughts rock.  I get off on the 3 second cast time alone, much less the mana ratio to damage.  But we are not talking about impressing you or me with showing spell damage, we are talking about impressing the rest of the group that is not a wizard.<br>
<br>
Group sees:<br>
Wizard casts Draught of Name_it (730)<br>
Mage_Pet says Rarr! 50,miss,70,30,55,miss,26,60,45,65,miss,60 ect...<br>
Mage casts Lava Bolt (810) or Shock of Steel (825)<br>
<br>
This starts at 51, and does not change at 59.  No one seeing this is going to care about mana ratio or cast time, and even if they did the pet would still sway them in the mages favor as it takes no mana to sustain. If they saw you do it twice in the time it took the mage to nuke once, you'd be accused by armchair wizards of overnuking...  At level 60 it's a new story, until level 61 and Firebolt of Tallon, and again, the group is not going to care about it being a bolt or anything else but the pretty number on their screen. <p><br>
